  "body": "In the `Deploy + Run transaction tab` in Remix:\r\n\r\nWhen sending a failing transaction via Remix (+ injected Provider - Metamask) to a contract on chain, a popup appears warning that the transaction reverts. You can either click `Send Transaction` or  `Cancel Transaction`.\r\n![ErrorPopupForRevertingTransaction](https://github.com/ethereum/remix-project/assets/13039169/37bab9b8-0ce0-47b9-81d4-a41e2628b68f)\r\n\r\nIf you click any of these two buttons in the popup, the Remix IDE continues to work correctly. But if you click outside of the focus area of the popup (or click the cancel button on the right top), the popup closes but from that point on the Remix IDE hangs. This means that when retrying to send the transaction again (or any other transaction), only a message in the Remix console appears `transact to Test.fail pending ...` but no reactions from metamask (or FailingTransactionWarningPopup appear).\r\n![ConsoleOutput](https://github.com/ethereum/remix-project/assets/13039169/5ba74a31-84bd-4bea-8c87-38a5ee7629b2)\r\n\r\n\r\nThe only solution I am aware of is to refresh the Remix page and reload my smart contract addresses of the already deployed contracts into the Remix IDE again. This is annoying when several contracts have been already loaded.",
